article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- — T.J. Bickerstaff's 19 points helped James Madison defeat Coastal Carolina 105-67 on Thursday night. Bickerstaff also contributed seven rebounds for the Dukes (19-3, 7-3 Sun Belt Conference). Noah Freidel shot 6 for 7, including 4 for 5 from beyond the arc to add 17 points. Terrence Edwards shot 7 for 10, including 2 for 3 from beyond the arc to finish with 16 points, while adding three steals. Jacob Meyer finished with 20 points for the Chanticleers (6-15, 3-7). Coastal Carolina also got 14 points from Kylan Blackmon. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
